{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"tfmhe5e71xfjajh6dar4sei","title":"Bowtie Problem","desc":"","updated":1734978555959,"created":1734768934772,"nav_order":6,"custom":{"nav_order":6},"fname":"International Trade Network.Decoding Complexity - Glattfelder.Ownership Networks.Bowtie Problem","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Decoding Complexity"},"contentHash":"bb1d5b25242b0cd5afb3603f4d71a6ac","links":[],"anchors":{"bowtie-problem-and-refinements-for-group-ownership":{"type":"header","text":"Bowtie problem and refinements for group ownership","value":"bowtie-problem-and-refinements-for-group-ownership","line":8,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["i6y65w9m41e586tibele629","c41jx1mfpsvb3uikovusctk"],"parent":"zj5v3rtroourx5kvsozplk9","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"bowtie-problem\">Bowtie Problem<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#bowtie-problem\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"bowtie-problem-and-refinements-for-group-ownership\">Bowtie problem and refinements for group ownership<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#bowtie-problem-and-refinements-for-group-ownership\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>(<span style=\"background-color: #bc42f5; color: black;\">Problem 2</span>). The <em>bow-tie</em> problem. \n<ul>\n<li>Consider this example of a network exhibiting a bow-tie topology:\n<img src=\"/Decoding-Complexity/assets/image-3.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></li>\n<li>A SCC (strongly connected component) lays in the center, with firms closely interconnected with one another; two firms (1) and (6) are not part of the SCC and are only loosely connected to the SCC through a single connection</li>\n<li>Applying the group ownership model on this example demonstrates the bow-tie problem\n<ul>\n<li>Suppose that the underlying value of each firm is 1: the column vector <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">v = (1,1,1,1,1,1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</li>\n<li>Using the ownership matrix given above, the uncorrected integrated value and network values are given to be\n<img src=\"/Decoding-Complexity/assets/image-4.png\" alt=\"alt text\">\nwhich are disproportionately high considering that the total underlying value of the network is <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1+1+1+1+1+1=6</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7278em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7278em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7278em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7278em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7278em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">6</span></span></span></span></span>, but e.g. the network value of the 5th firm reaches 55, an order of magnitude larger.</li>\n<li>Introducing the correction operator<img src=\"/Decoding-Complexity/assets/image-5.png\" alt=\"alt text\">\nleads to the corrected integrated and network values\n<img src=\"/Decoding-Complexity/assets/image-6.png\" alt=\"alt text\">\nreduced by approx. one order of magnitude.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The issue lies with firm 1: it is not part of the SCC and only owns a very small share in firm 2, as shown. However, the correction operator does not correct its values at all (because firm 1 is a <em>root node</em>, a node where there are no incoming connections) and thus the integrated value and network values of firm 1 are both the largest among the group after corrections\n<ul>\n<li>The formula for integrated value means that as firm 1 owns a small share of firm 2 (part of the SCC), the integrated value of the entire SCC is added to firm 1</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>This is clearly undesireable, as firm 1 is not very involved in the group and should not have this high of a network value</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/Decoding-Complexity/notes/c41jx1mfpsvb3uikovusctk\">Flow in Ownership Networks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Decoding-Complexity/notes/i6y65w9m41e586tibele629\">Algorithms for Bowtie Problem</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"7158c8fk0m4y0idefh3sf12","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1734711013618,"created":1734710800576,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Decoding Complexity"},"contentHash":"c30a43132883b1e15a6a99a3d78c8ad6","links":[],"anchors":{"landing-page":{"type":"header","text":"Landing page","value":"landing-page","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["k6p67151vpxebl